msgSnippet: 1) JUnit generally isn t thought of as a performance test tool, though there are extensions to it to help in that area. 2) JUnit is only for Java.  You should
messageBody:
1) JUnit generally isn't thought of as a performance test tool, though
there are extensions to it to help in that area.

2) JUnit is only for Java. You should look into NUnit, located here:
http://www.nunit.org/.


Todd.
